JEDDAH: Virtual reality made a guest appearance at the Hajj Expo 2023 in Jeddah, the Saudi Press Agency reported on Thursday. Madinah’s International Fair and Museum of the Prophet’s Biography and Islamic Civilization provided visitors with a unique opportunity to learn about the Prophet Muhammad’s life using the technology at its pavilion at the Hajj and Umrah services conference. Virtual reality displayed scenes from the Prophet’s Chamber, giving visitors the chance to immerse themselves in Islam’s values and practices while also exploring rare artifacts mentioned in the Qur’an and the Sunnah. The display at the pavilion provided a glimpse of how contemporary techniques will be used to project Islam and its culture in the future. 